<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Rgeos on KevCaz's Website</title><link>https://kevcaz.github.io/tags/rgeos/</link><description>Recent content in Rgeos on KevCaz's Website</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><copyright>Content under CC0 1.0 Universal unless otherwise specified.</copyright><lastBuildDate>Sat, 02 Feb 2019 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://kevcaz.github.io/tags/rgeos/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>rgeos v0.4-2</title><link>https://kevcaz.github.io/notes/2019/02/2019-02-02_rgeos_v0_4/</link><pubDate>Sat, 02 Feb 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://kevcaz.github.io/notes/2019/02/2019-02-02_rgeos_v0_4/</guid><description>&lt;p>As explained in a &lt;a href="../../notes/r/rgeos">previous note&lt;/a>, a few weeks ago I was not able to install &lt;a href="https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/rgeos/index.html">&lt;code>rgeos&lt;/code>&lt;/a> version 0.4-1. I ran into a new issue today and I decided to figure out what was wrong with it. After a quick search, I found &lt;a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/53042751/when-trying-to-install-rgeos-r-cannot-find-lgeos">this answer on &lt;i class="fa fa-stack-overflow" aria-hidden="true">&lt;/i>&lt;/a> and it turned out that all I needed was to install &lt;a href="https://packages.debian.org/sid/libgeos++-dev">libgeos++-dev&lt;/a> and so I did:&lt;/p>
&lt;pre tabindex="0">&lt;code>sudo apt install libgeos++-dev
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;p>After that the command:&lt;/p>
&lt;pre tabindex="0">&lt;code>Rscript -e &amp;#34;install.packages(&amp;#39;rgeos&amp;#39;)&amp;#34;
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;p>worked like a charm! I guess this is mentioned somewhere in the doc, I obviously missed something (as far as I understand, &lt;code>libgeos++-dev&lt;/code> was not required before version v0.4-x, only &lt;code>libgeos-dev&lt;/code>). Anyway, once again, thanks to the &lt;i class="fa fa-stack-overflow" aria-hidden="true">&lt;/i> users!&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Something wrong with rgeos 0.4-1?</title><link>https://kevcaz.github.io/notes/2018/11/2018-11-07_something_wrong_with/</link><pubDate>Wed, 07 Nov 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://kevcaz.github.io/notes/2018/11/2018-11-07_something_wrong_with/</guid><description>&lt;p>The last update of &lt;a href="https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/rgeos/index.html">rgeos (version 0.4-1)&lt;/a>
